  { q: "Does Ferrari always hold its value in Australia?", a: "No. Ferrari is one of the strongest prestige marques, but value varies sharply by model, kilometres, specification, condition, service history and Australian delivery status. Limited-production, manual, special-series and well documented cars usually have stronger demand than common or poorly maintained examples." },
  { q: "Is Porsche safer than Ferrari from a resale perspective?", a: "Not necessarily. Porsche often has broader liquidity, especially around the 911, but there are many Porsche variants. GT, RS, Turbo S, limited-production and rare manual examples can be strong. Standard models need more careful assessment." },
